body:
>  Does Yii use a pdo prepared statement internally even without we use a :placeholder?

Yeap, as far as i see in the code Yii converts all values to placeholders and then executes query as usual pdo statement

https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/master/framework/db/QueryBuilder.php#L1239

```
        foreach ($values as $value) {
            if ($value instanceof Expression) {
                foreach ($value->params as $n => $v) {
                    $params[$n] = $v;
                }
                $phName = $value->expression;
            } else {
                $phName = self::PARAM_PREFIX . count($params);
                $params[$phName] = empty($escape) ? $value : ('%' . strtr($value, $escape) . '%');
            }
            $parts[] = "$column $operator $phName";
        }
```
